<subSubSection box="[160,1053,521,581]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1053,521,581]" box="[160,285,521,547]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,521,547]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1053,521,581]" box="[160,1053,556,581]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">
The new species is named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Islam &amp; Ahmad" authorityYear="2022" box="[463,777,556,581]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="brevicaudatus">
<emphasis box="[463,777,556,581]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">Dorylaimoides brevicaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of its short tail.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="339" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1157,641,1672]" box="[160,489,641,667]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,489,641,667]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">Diagnosis and relationships</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1157,641,1672]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">
<taxonomicName authority="Islam &amp; Ahmad, 2022" authorityName="Islam &amp; Ahmad" authorityYear="2022" box="[160,478,676,701]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="brevicaudatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[160,478,676,701]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">Dorylaimoides brevicaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[489,580,676,701]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is characterised by having a slender body, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.045" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="0.99" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" unit="mm" value="1.045" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.99">0.99– 1.1 mm</quantity>
long; lip region cap-like, almost continuous or offset by slight depression; odontostyle 7.5–8.5 μm, ventral arm 5.0–5.5 µm, dorsal arm 6.0–6.5 µm; odontophore 10.5–12.5 μm long, arcuate; total stylet length 18.5–20.0 μm; pharynx slender with slightly muscular anterior part, expanding gradually into a short, cylindrical basal bulb occupying about 25–30% of total neck length; female genital system didelphic-amphidelphic; tail short, convex-conoid with rounded terminus, males with 24.5–30 µm long spicules, lateral guiding pieces and 5–7 irregularly spaced ventromedian supplements.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1157,641,1672]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">
In the presence of short expanded part of pharynx and short, rounded to conoid tail, the new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Ahmad et al., 2003" authorityName="Ahmad" authorityYear="2003" box="[468,877,988,1013]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="cameroonensis">
<emphasis box="[468,660,988,1013]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">D. cameroonensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ahmad W &amp; Mushtaq P &amp; Baniyamuddin M" box="[667,877,988,1013]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" pagination="153 - 162" refId="ref17976" refString="Ahmad W, Mushtaq P, Baniyamuddin M. 2003. Descriptions of three new species of Dorylaimoides Thorne &amp; Swanger, 1936 (Nematoda: Dorylaimida). J Nem Morph Syst. 5: 153 - 162." type="journal article" year="2003">Ahmad et al., 2003</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Siddiqi, 1964" authorityName="Siddiqi" authorityYear="1964" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="parateres">
<emphasis box="[934,1065,988,1013]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">D. parateres</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Siddiqi MR" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" pagination="626 - 634" refId="ref19460" refString="Siddiqi MR. 1964. Three new species of Dorylaimoides Thorne &amp; Swanger, 1936, with descriptions of Xiphinema orbum n. sp. (Nematoda: Dorylaimoidea). Nematologica. 9 (4): 626 - 634. doi: 10.1163 / 187529263 X 00737." type="journal article" year="1964">Siddiqi, 1964</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from the former in having a long and slender body (L = 0.91–1.1 vs 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.149999999999999" metricValueMax="8.7" metricValueMin="7.6" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" unit="mm" value="0.815" valueMax="0.87" valueMin="0.76">0.76– 0.87 mm</quantity>
, a = 33–39 vs 25–29), narrower lip region (7.0–8.0 vs 9.0–11 μm), shorter odontostyle (7.5–8.5 vs 10–11 μm) and higher b (5.7–6.9 vs 4.6–5.5) and c (64–79 vs 43– 60) ratios.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1157,641,1672]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">
The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Siddiqi" authorityYear="1964" box="[521,652,1162,1187]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="parateres">
<emphasis box="[521,652,1162,1187]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">D. parateres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a shorter body (L = 0.9–1.1 vs 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" unit="mm" value="1.4" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.2">1.2– 1.6 mm</quantity>
), slightly posterior vulva position (V = 47–51 vs 39–48), lower c’ ratio (0.7–0.9 vs 1.0–1.5), shorter and differently shaped tail (15–17 vs 27–29 μm long, convex-conoid to rounded vs rounded to hemispheroid) and smaller spicules (24.5–30 vs 35–36 μm).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1157,641,1672]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">
In the presence of amphidelphic gonads and a short tail, the new species also resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Jairajpuri, 1965" authorityName="Jairajpuri" authorityYear="1965" box="[282,569,1335,1360]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="indicus">
<emphasis box="[282,390,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">D. indicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jairajpuri MS" box="[398,569,1335,1360]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" pagination="124 - 125" refId="ref18902" refString="Jairajpuri MS. 1965. Dorylaimoides indicus n. sp. (Nematode: Dorylaimoidea) from India. Lab J Sci Tech. 3: 124 - 125." type="journal article" year="1965">Jairajpuri, 1965</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Thorne and Swanger, 1936" authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" box="[628,1025,1335,1360]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="teres">
<emphasis box="[628,710,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">D. teres</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thorne G &amp; Swanger HH" box="[719,1025,1335,1360]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" pagination="223" refId="ref19695" refString="Thorne G, Swanger HH. 1936. A monograph of the nematode genera Dorylaimus Dujardin, Aporcelaimus n. g., Dorylaimoides n. g., and Pungentus n. g. Cap Zoologica. 6: 223." type="journal article" year="1936">Thorne and Swanger, 1936</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the former in having a shorter body (L = 0.9–1.1 vs 
<quantity box="[792,925,1370,1395]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.8 mm</quantity>
), shorter pharyngeal expansion (41–50 vs 64 μm or 24–30 vs 31% of total neck length), slightly posterior vulva position (V = 47–51 vs 39–47), shorter tail (15–17 vs 18–26 μm) and smaller spicules (24.5– 30 vs 38 μm).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[160,1157,641,1672]" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">
The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" box="[514,593,1508,1533]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="teres">
<emphasis box="[514,593,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="339">D. teres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a comparatively shorter body (0.9–1.1 vs 
<quantity box="[160,295,1543,1568]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="28" pageNumber="339" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.6 mm</quantity>
), differently shaped and narrower lip region (conoid vs rounded, 7.0–8.0 vs 9.0–10 μm), shorter pharyngeal expansion (41–50 vs 51–63 μm), slightly posterior vulva position (V = 47–51 vs 40–48), shorter tail (15–17 vs 21–30 μm) and smaller spicules (24.5– 30 vs 35–38 μm).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
